{"TopicId":209596,"ForumId":112,"TopicTitle":"Aerospikes?","CreatedByName":"Rutabaga22","CreatedById":221143,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-01T20:16:24Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Rutabaga22","CreatedById":221143,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-01T20:16:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI feel like in ksp2 we need more aerospikes. There could be so many shapes\u0027s and sizes that would add a lot more depth to using an aerospike. I would at least like an aerospike for every ksp 1 size and shape.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ryaja","CreatedById":221431,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-01T21:07:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would be awesome but we would also be modular linear aerospikes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Zozaf Kerman","CreatedById":219910,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-01T21:27:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe could maybe get some procedural aerospikes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rutabaga22","CreatedById":221143,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-01T21:31:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224169775\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209596\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221662066467\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022221431\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ryaja\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n24 minutes ago, Ryaja said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nlinear aerospikes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTHis is one of the big ones, linear aerospikes should be provided in at least Mk2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"intelliCom","CreatedById":209738,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-01T22:39:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know this isn\u0027t quite an aerospike, but the idea is similar;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nConvair Nexus plug nozzle, 7.5m wide.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022nexus2.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022131.58\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u0022513\u0022 src=\u0022https://up-ship.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/01/nexus2.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rutabaga22","CreatedById":221143,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-01T22:57:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224169800\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209596\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221662071970\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022209738\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022intelliCom\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, intelliCom said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know this isn\u0027t quite an aerospike, but the idea is similar;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nConvair Nexus plug nozzle, 7.5m wide.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://up-ship.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/01/nexus2.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022nexus2.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022131.58\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u0022513\u0022 src=\u0022https://up-ship.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/01/nexus2.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat wou;d be very welcome, I would love these old, wild concepts in ksp2 or as a ksp1 mod\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GaussFlux","CreatedById":222777,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-06T21:11:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHonestly I\u0027d love to see large aerospikes and especially plug nozzles like what was proposed for the ROMBUS and phoenix SSTOs, the would be great for automated heavy lift as the engine doubles as a heatshield allowing for easy reuse.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Douglas ROMBUS | Secret Projects Forum\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 width=\u0022500\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.secretprojects.co.uk/data/attachments/29/29546-a7710101a884da9b850637b65233de42.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sturmhauke","CreatedById":190611,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-07T19:46:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224169784\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209596\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221662067898\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022221143\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rutabaga22\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/1/2022 at 2:31 PM, Rutabaga22 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTHis is one of the big ones, linear aerospikes should be provided in at least Mk2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI move that they be called \u0022aeroblades\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}